# TypeScript Config Package Rules

## Architecture
- Shared TypeScript configurations
- Base configs for different project types
- Standardized compiler options
- Consistent type checking across monorepo

## Available Configurations
- `base.json` - Base TypeScript configuration
- `nextjs.json` - Next.js specific configuration
- `nestjs.json` - NestJS backend configuration
- `react-library.json` - React library configuration

## Usage Patterns
```json
{
  "extends": "@repo/typescript-config/nextjs.json"
}
```

## Configuration Standards
- Enable strict mode for all configs
- Use consistent module resolution
- Proper path mapping for monorepo
- Enable incremental compilation
- Configure proper output directories

## Type Safety
- Enable all strict type checks
- Use consistent lib configurations
- Proper JSX settings for React projects
- Enable source map generation
- Use consistent target versions

## Path Resolution
- Configure proper baseUrl settings
- Use path mapping for internal packages
- Support absolute imports where needed
- Maintain consistent import patterns

## Build Settings
- Optimize for development speed
- Enable proper output generation
- Configure declaration file generation
- Support proper tree shaking
- Enable proper source maps

## Linting Integration
- Work with ESLint configurations
- Support Prettier integration
- Enable proper type checking in editors
- Support import sorting

## Performance
- Enable incremental compilation
- Use proper build caching
- Optimize type checking speed
- Configure proper exclude patterns

## Maintenance
- Keep TypeScript version consistent
- Update compiler options as needed
- Test configurations across all packages
- Document breaking changes
- Follow semantic versioning